    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
<p>@Nikita's comment in the question works. In the following code, I also considered sorting the messages by time (including the AM/PM tag):</p>

<pre class="lang-php s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-php">        <span class="hljs-comment">// Sort messages by date</span>
            <span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">usort</span>(<span class="hljs-variable">$MessagesArray</span>, function (<span class="hljs-variable">$a</span>, <span class="hljs-variable">$b</span>) {
                <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> <span class="hljs-variable">$a</span>[<span class="hljs-string">'date'</span>] &lt;=&gt; <span class="hljs-variable">$b</span>[<span class="hljs-string">'date'</span>];
            });
        <span class="hljs-comment">// Sort messages by date and time</span>
            <span class="hljs-comment">// Obtain a list of columns</span>
            <span class="hljs-keyword">foreach</span> (<span class="hljs-variable">$MessagesArray</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">as</span> <span class="hljs-variable">$key</span> =&gt; <span class="hljs-variable">$row</span>) {
                <span class="hljs-variable">$date</span>[<span class="hljs-variable">$key</span>]  = <span class="hljs-variable">$row</span>[<span class="hljs-string">'date'</span>];
                <span class="hljs-variable">$time</span>[<span class="hljs-variable">$key</span>] = <span class="hljs-variable">$row</span>[<span class="hljs-string">'time'</span>];
            }
            <span class="hljs-comment">// Sort the messages</span>
            <span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">array_multisort</span>(<span class="hljs-variable">$date</span>, SORT_ASC, <span class="hljs-variable">$time</span>, SORT_ASC, <span class="hljs-variable">$MessagesArray</span>);
</code></pre>

<p>Keep in mind @Scoots' and @Elementary's comments also already sort them by date.</p>
    </div>
